00:23:08.567 --> 00:23:10.074
- This is Brexton.

00:23:10.074 --> 00:23:13.741
He's 22 months old and
this is our Cole Cole

00:23:14.582 --> 00:23:15.832
and he is five.

00:23:16.875 --> 00:23:18.763
- My son, Cole, was born
with a genetic condition

00:23:18.763 --> 00:23:20.419
called Fragile X Syndrome.

00:23:20.419 --> 00:23:22.494
My family and other families
hope to teach you more

00:23:22.494 --> 00:23:23.919
about this condition.

00:23:23.919 --> 00:23:26.881
Fragile X Syndrome is a genetic condition

00:23:26.881 --> 00:23:29.740
that causes intellectual
disability, behavioral,

00:23:29.740 --> 00:23:31.066
and learning challenges

00:23:31.066 --> 00:23:33.308
and various physical characteristics.

00:23:33.308 --> 00:23:35.419
Though Fragile X occurs in both genders,

00:23:35.419 --> 00:23:38.185
males are more frequently
affected than females

00:23:38.185 --> 00:23:40.745
and generally with greater severity.

00:23:40.745 --> 00:23:42.609
Life expectancy is not affected in people

00:23:42.609 --> 00:23:44.418
with Fragile X Syndrome
because there are usually

00:23:44.418 --> 00:23:46.203
no life threatening
health concerns associated

00:23:46.203 --> 00:23:47.779
with the condition.

00:23:47.779 --> 00:23:52.215
Fragile X Syndrome is caused
by mutations in the FMR1 gene.

00:23:52.215 --> 00:23:55.336
This condition has an unusual

00:23:55.336 --> 00:23:57.374
non-Mendelian inheritance pattern.

00:23:57.374 --> 00:24:00.420
Almost all cases are
caused by an expansion

00:24:00.420 --> 00:24:03.079
of the FMR1 gene on the X chromosome.

00:24:03.079 --> 00:24:06.401
Usually the FMR1 gene
includes repetitive series

00:24:06.401 --> 00:24:09.486
of CGG triplets which is
repeated in most people

00:24:09.486 --> 00:24:11.403
from five to 45 times.

00:24:11.403 --> 00:24:13.655
Individuals with Fragile X Syndrome

00:24:13.655 --> 00:24:15.155
have more than 200 repeats,

00:24:15.155 --> 00:24:18.117
silencing the activity of this gene.

00:24:18.117 --> 00:24:20.012
- [Female] Fragile X Syndrome
is diagnosed in about

00:24:20.012 --> 00:24:23.738
one in 4,000 males and
one in 8,000 females.

00:24:23.738 --> 00:24:26.585
Females typically have
milder symptoms than males,

00:24:26.585 --> 00:24:28.643
although some females may have

00:24:28.643 --> 00:24:32.560
additional behavioral
features such as shyness.

00:24:34.218 --> 00:24:38.385
Cole was diagnosed with Fragile
X when he was 22 months old.

00:24:40.155 --> 00:24:42.655
He was not walking or talking.

00:24:44.075 --> 00:24:45.761
He started with the ear
infections the month

00:24:45.761 --> 00:24:49.290
after he turned one and
for the next few months,

00:24:49.290 --> 00:24:52.836
he was on antibiotics probably
four out of the five months

00:24:52.836 --> 00:24:57.113
and we noticed that he
wasn't really responding,

00:24:57.113 --> 00:24:59.196
we didn't understand why.

00:25:00.956 --> 00:25:03.733
We had visited a neurologist just because

00:25:03.733 --> 00:25:06.214
the primary care physician
was a little bit confused

00:25:06.214 --> 00:25:08.298
where to put him and she said,

00:25:08.298 --> 00:25:10.620
"Well, he definitely doesn't have autism

00:25:10.620 --> 00:25:12.728
"if that's why you're here but go through

00:25:12.728 --> 00:25:17.442
"with the tube surgery and
see what happens there but,

00:25:17.442 --> 00:25:18.730
"in the meantime,

00:25:18.730 --> 00:25:20.853
"why don't we do these genetic testing

00:25:20.853 --> 00:25:23.765
"while you already have
him under anesthesia."

00:25:23.765 --> 00:25:26.958
And so, within 24 hours of
him having the ear surgery,

00:25:26.958 --> 00:25:30.524
the tube surgery, he was
walking without support.

00:25:30.524 --> 00:25:34.299
So we assumed that it was all
to do with all that fluid.

00:25:34.299 --> 00:25:35.751
Maybe two weeks after the surgery,

00:25:35.751 --> 00:25:39.967
the neurologist called and
was completely baffled,

00:25:39.967 --> 00:25:42.060
said that she was completely shocked,

00:25:42.060 --> 00:25:44.862
was not expecting that
result at all but that

00:25:44.862 --> 00:25:47.843
he had the full mutation of Fragile X.

00:25:47.843 --> 00:25:49.772
Cole's number was 300.

00:25:49.772 --> 00:25:51.790
- The diagnosis didn't change who he was

00:25:51.790 --> 00:25:54.475
and he was still a super fun, happy kid

00:25:54.475 --> 00:25:57.475
and then so we kind of accepted that

00:26:00.267 --> 00:26:03.804
and have been working towards
getting the most help we can

00:26:03.804 --> 00:26:07.650
at the early age where
it can help the most.

00:26:07.650 --> 00:26:08.737
- Hi, I'm Brian.

00:26:08.737 --> 00:26:10.027
- I'm Haley.

00:26:10.027 --> 00:26:11.726
- Justin's 15.

00:26:11.726 --> 00:26:15.099
We got diagnosed with
Fragile X on or around

00:26:15.099 --> 00:26:16.227
when he was five years old

00:26:16.227 --> 00:26:18.091
after his first Grand Mal seizure.

00:26:18.091 --> 00:26:20.672
About 20% of all kids with
Fragile X have seizures.

00:26:20.672 --> 00:26:22.902
Haley's been an amazing sister.

00:26:22.902 --> 00:26:26.418
She has always supported Justin fully

00:26:26.418 --> 00:26:29.489
and she even has a saying which is,

00:26:29.489 --> 00:26:32.898
Justin is her social barometer
and if there was anybody

00:26:32.898 --> 00:26:35.750
who wanted to be her
friend, come into the house,

00:26:35.750 --> 00:26:36.936
or be a part of her life,

00:26:36.936 --> 00:26:38.317
- He has to meet Justin.

00:26:38.317 --> 00:26:40.553
- If they did not get along
with Justin or accept Justin

00:26:40.553 --> 00:26:41.971
for who he was,

00:26:41.971 --> 00:26:43.179
that was the end of that relationship

00:26:43.179 --> 00:26:45.052
and she would move onto whomever

00:26:45.052 --> 00:26:47.846
would be open and welcoming.

00:26:47.846 --> 00:26:50.400
Many males with Fragile X
Syndrome are likely to have

00:26:50.400 --> 00:26:51.616
the following features:

00:26:51.616 --> 00:26:55.873
long, narrow face, large ears,
prominent jaws and forehead.

00:26:55.873 --> 00:26:57.986
Approximately half of
females with Fragile X

00:26:57.986 --> 00:26:59.703
also have these features.

00:26:59.703 --> 00:27:03.035
flexible fingers, flat
feet and enlarged testicles

00:27:03.035 --> 00:27:05.318
can also be seen after puberty.

00:27:05.318 --> 00:27:08.113
These features may become
more apparent with age.

00:27:08.113 --> 00:27:10.079
- [Haley] Pre-pubertal males
tend to have normal growth

00:27:10.079 --> 00:27:12.541
but large occipitofrontal
head circumference.

00:27:12.541 --> 00:27:13.458
- I'm Tara.

00:27:14.457 --> 00:27:15.817
- I'm Steve.

00:27:15.817 --> 00:27:17.051
- I'm Jason.

00:27:17.051 --> 00:27:18.530
- Andrew.

00:27:18.530 --> 00:27:20.863
- Andrew was diagnosed first

00:27:22.039 --> 00:27:24.872
with the autism spectrum disorder,

00:27:26.547 --> 00:27:30.714
just the generic PDDNOS and
the doctor we were seeing said,

00:27:32.521 --> 00:27:34.861
"I think you need some other testing.

00:27:34.861 --> 00:27:37.316
"He doesn't quite fit
all the characteristics

00:27:37.316 --> 00:27:38.913
"'cause he's so social."

00:27:38.913 --> 00:27:41.886
Lo and behold, we got a
call that they were shocked

00:27:41.886 --> 00:27:46.053
that he had it and so that began
our journey with Fragile X.

00:27:52.197 --> 00:27:54.614
Jason was born and they said,

00:27:54.614 --> 00:27:56.603
oh, he's probably gonna be a carrier.

00:27:56.603 --> 00:27:59.246
- [Steve] It turned out
that he was full Fragile X.

00:27:59.246 --> 00:28:00.197
- [Tara] Yes.

00:28:00.197 --> 00:28:01.378
- [Steve] Whereas Andrew is a

00:28:01.378 --> 00:28:02.867
mosaic.
- [Tara] Mosaic.

00:28:02.867 --> 00:28:06.761
So two completely different presentations

00:28:06.761 --> 00:28:09.290
and two completely different answers.

00:28:09.290 --> 00:28:11.752
- A highly characteristic
behavioral feature

00:28:11.752 --> 00:28:14.425
of Fragile X is males and
females is gaze aversion,

00:28:14.425 --> 00:28:17.610
a distinctive type of poor
eye contact where the person

00:28:17.610 --> 00:28:19.407
actively diverts his or her eyes.

00:28:19.407 --> 00:28:22.756
Hand flapping and hand
biting are nearly universal

00:28:22.756 --> 00:28:26.038
in young boys and most
girls with Fragile X.

00:28:26.038 --> 00:28:27.990
While the physical features
of Fragile X Syndrome

00:28:27.990 --> 00:28:30.139
can be very subtle in
pre-pubertal children,

00:28:30.139 --> 00:28:32.304
the triad of gaze aversion,

00:28:32.304 --> 00:28:34.216
hand flapping and hand
biting in young children

00:28:34.216 --> 00:28:36.459
with global developmental delay,

00:28:36.459 --> 00:28:39.133
is highly suggestive
of Fragile X Syndrome.

00:28:39.133 --> 00:28:43.384
Expressive language has
been delayed significantly.

00:28:43.384 --> 00:28:46.213
It seems as if that has
been his biggest hit

00:28:46.213 --> 00:28:50.081
but it's coming and so
he's at the point now

00:28:50.081 --> 00:28:51.266
where he'll ask questions.

00:28:51.266 --> 00:28:52.258
So that's coming.

00:28:52.258 --> 00:28:55.366
The other thing is the
attention and the hyperactivity

00:28:55.366 --> 00:28:59.304
and he definitely has
both of those things,

00:28:59.304 --> 00:29:02.549
especially in a learning
environment where the classroom

00:29:02.549 --> 00:29:06.224
is structured so that you have eight desks

00:29:06.224 --> 00:29:08.532
all sitting in one direction,
listening to a lecture,

00:29:08.532 --> 00:29:13.094
and that's probably not
going to fit him. (laughs)

00:29:13.094 --> 00:29:15.960
- So one of the advantages
is, he loves electronics.

00:29:15.960 --> 00:29:19.453
So any kind of therapeutic stuff

00:29:19.453 --> 00:29:23.120
that we can get on the
iPads and on his iPod

00:29:24.683 --> 00:29:26.874
work out well for him 'cause he likes

00:29:26.874 --> 00:29:29.296
to do the electronic piece.

00:29:29.296 --> 00:29:31.311
He's more of a follower.

00:29:31.311 --> 00:29:33.365
He likes to watch him
do the stuff. (laughs)

00:29:33.365 --> 00:29:37.532
- Andrew's mainstreamed for
social studies and science

00:29:38.525 --> 00:29:41.177
and art and music and gym.

00:29:41.177 --> 00:29:45.240
Part of the day he goes to his
support classes for reading,

00:29:45.240 --> 00:29:46.657
math and english.

00:29:47.755 --> 00:29:49.493
- One of the most interesting
things about Justin is,

00:29:49.493 --> 00:29:52.583
in order for him to
cognitively figure things out,

00:29:52.583 --> 00:29:54.854
he does it in forms of
questions and I know this

00:29:54.854 --> 00:29:56.455
is very typical with Fragile X

00:29:56.455 --> 00:29:59.084
and so he has a set of questions
that he will go through

00:29:59.084 --> 00:30:01.877
over and over and over
again but it's a way for him

00:30:01.877 --> 00:30:03.161
to get information.

00:30:03.161 --> 00:30:04.132
Right, Justin?

00:30:04.132 --> 00:30:05.235
- Mm Hmm (affirmative).

00:30:05.235 --> 00:30:06.183
- Awesome, right?

00:30:06.183 --> 00:30:07.156
Can I get a high five?

00:30:07.156 --> 00:30:09.944
- [Tara] When there is
an interest in a subject,

00:30:09.944 --> 00:30:14.111
there's a zero in on a focus
for what they can learn

00:30:16.066 --> 00:30:18.696
and what they really can do.

00:30:18.696 --> 00:30:21.235
- So it's a matter of just
finding what interests them

00:30:21.235 --> 00:30:24.923
and then using it to your
advantage to help them

00:30:24.923 --> 00:30:27.333
improve their skills.

00:30:27.333 --> 00:30:28.559
- [Haley] With Fragile X Syndrome,

00:30:28.559 --> 00:30:31.730
there is also a higher prevalence
of mitral valve prolapse

00:30:31.730 --> 00:30:32.994
than in the general population.

00:30:32.994 --> 00:30:36.483
Other medical conditions
that can be seen as part of

00:30:36.483 --> 00:30:37.868
Fragile X Syndrome include:

00:30:37.868 --> 00:30:42.228
recurrent otitis media
and hypotonia in infancy.

00:30:42.228 --> 00:30:45.102
Approximately 15% of
males and 5% of females

00:30:45.102 --> 00:30:47.385
with Fragile X have seizures.

00:30:47.385 --> 00:30:49.201
- I typically look at
three different levers

00:30:49.201 --> 00:30:52.091
when you think about anyone
associated with Fragile X.

00:30:52.091 --> 00:30:55.848
You have an anxiety lever,
you have a behavioral lever,

00:30:55.848 --> 00:31:00.368
and then you have a mental
impairment lever and so,

00:31:00.368 --> 00:31:02.082
because it's a syndrome, you know,

00:31:02.082 --> 00:31:05.563
everyone affected by Fragile
X has a different portion

00:31:05.563 --> 00:31:07.701
of each of those levers and so,

00:31:07.701 --> 00:31:09.982
in Justin's case, he
has debilitating anxiety

00:31:09.982 --> 00:31:12.338
which really hurts him
with the transitions

00:31:12.338 --> 00:31:15.002
and actually just being
ready to do things.

00:31:15.002 --> 00:31:16.407
On the mental impairment side,

00:31:16.407 --> 00:31:18.984
he's actually higher on
the cognitive ability.

00:31:18.984 --> 00:31:22.478
His puzzle ability, his ability
to think, it's all in there.

00:31:22.478 --> 00:31:23.797
We say that all the time.

00:31:23.797 --> 00:31:25.195
Just waiting for it to all, to come out,

00:31:25.195 --> 00:31:28.141
but his behaviors
associated with his anxiety

00:31:28.141 --> 00:31:31.671
are typically very bad
especially when he was younger.

00:31:31.671 --> 00:31:33.582
- [Haley] Behaviors in males
with Fragile X Syndrome

00:31:33.582 --> 00:31:34.533
often include:

00:31:34.533 --> 00:31:38.195
tactile defensiveness, poor
eye contact, repetitive speech,

00:31:38.195 --> 00:31:40.567
problems in impulse control
control and distractibility.

00:31:40.567 --> 00:31:44.504
A majority of boys and many
girls with Fragile X Syndrome

00:31:44.504 --> 00:31:47.504
exhibit features of
autism spectrum disorder.

00:31:47.504 --> 00:31:48.556
- It takes time to figure it out,

00:31:48.556 --> 00:31:50.377
figure out what works for your kid,

00:31:50.377 --> 00:31:53.567
'cause every kid truly is different.

00:31:53.567 --> 00:31:57.734
We have two and they
respond differently (laughs)

00:31:59.165 --> 00:32:01.633
to different things just
like any other two kids

00:32:01.633 --> 00:32:05.164
we would've had would respond differently.

00:32:05.164 --> 00:32:07.205
- He's brightened many
a people's life, I feel,

00:32:07.205 --> 00:32:09.543
