00:39:10.811 --> 00:39:13.388
Chromosomes are the instructions
that tell our bodies

00:39:13.388 --> 00:39:15.084
how to grow and develop.

00:39:15.084 --> 00:39:18.920
Most people have two
copies of each chromosome

00:39:18.920 --> 00:39:21.132
for a total of 46 chromosomes.

00:39:21.132 --> 00:39:24.303
Some people have 47 chromosomes.

00:39:24.303 --> 00:39:26.991
Most people who have Down Syndrome,

00:39:26.991 --> 00:39:31.158
have three copies of chromosome
21 also known as Trisomy 21.

00:39:34.197 --> 00:39:38.615
This is caused by a sporadic
event known as non-disjunction

00:39:38.615 --> 00:39:42.032
which usually occurs prior to conception.

00:39:44.711 --> 00:39:47.982
- Each child is unique
and special (laughs)

00:39:47.982 --> 00:39:51.583
and has specific needs that are different.

00:39:51.583 --> 00:39:53.894
Get to know the person
that you're working with.

00:39:53.894 --> 00:39:57.977
The diagnosis can be the
same but each individual

00:39:58.863 --> 00:40:01.097
is an individual.

00:40:01.097 --> 00:40:03.025
Children with Down Syndrome are expected

00:40:03.025 --> 00:40:06.118
to reach developmental
milestones as other children,

00:40:06.118 --> 00:40:08.541
however, it may take a little bit longer

00:40:08.541 --> 00:40:10.208
than other children.

00:40:11.951 --> 00:40:13.566
People with Down Syndrome

00:40:13.566 --> 00:40:16.494
have characteristic facial features.

00:40:16.494 --> 00:40:18.831
For example, you may see folds of the skin

00:40:18.831 --> 00:40:23.252
on the inner corner of their
eyes called epicanthal folds.

00:40:23.252 --> 00:40:25.822
You may notice that the
nose looks a little flatter

00:40:25.822 --> 00:40:27.827
at the top between the eyes.

00:40:27.827 --> 00:40:31.160
This is called a depressed nasal bridge.

00:40:32.056 --> 00:40:35.787
Individuals may have eyes
that slant slightly upward

00:40:35.787 --> 00:40:40.145
which is called upslanting
palpebral fissures.

00:40:40.145 --> 00:40:44.706
Another physical feature
commonly seen in Down Syndrome

00:40:44.706 --> 00:40:47.411
is called a single palmar crease.

00:40:47.411 --> 00:40:50.636
This used to be called a simian
crease but has been changed

00:40:50.636 --> 00:40:53.322
to better describe this feature.

00:40:53.322 --> 00:40:55.840
This is when someone has one crease

00:40:55.840 --> 00:40:57.996
that goes across the hand.

00:40:57.996 --> 00:41:00.911
About half of people with
Down Syndrome have this crease

00:41:00.911 --> 00:41:03.160
on at least one hand.

00:41:03.160 --> 00:41:05.946
It develops during the fetal period.

00:41:05.946 --> 00:41:08.475
These features don't
cause problems in children

00:41:08.475 --> 00:41:09.867
with Down Syndrome.

00:41:09.867 --> 00:41:11.569
People without the syndrome

00:41:11.569 --> 00:41:14.689
can also have some of
these features as well.

