00:42:20.232 --> 00:42:23.943
- Some health problems are
more common among people

00:42:23.943 --> 00:42:28.236
with Down Syndrome than
the general population.

00:42:28.236 --> 00:42:31.781
Between 40 and 60% of children
born with Down Syndrome

00:42:31.781 --> 00:42:34.311
will have a congenital heart defect.

00:42:34.311 --> 00:42:36.851
About five to 10% of
people with Down Syndrome

00:42:36.851 --> 00:42:39.221
are born with an intestinal blockage

00:42:39.221 --> 00:42:42.033
called duodenal atresia,

00:42:42.033 --> 00:42:44.317
others will have gastroesophageal reflux.

00:42:44.317 --> 00:42:49.019
Some other specific digestive
conditions can also be seen

00:42:49.019 --> 00:42:53.179
more commonly than in
the general population.

00:42:53.179 --> 00:42:55.624
AV canal, a specific heart defect,

00:42:55.624 --> 00:42:59.687
is more common in babies with
Down Syndrome than without.

00:42:59.687 --> 00:43:02.740
An AV canal occurs when
the septum that separates

00:43:02.740 --> 00:43:06.015
the left and right sides of
the heart has a hole in it.

00:43:06.015 --> 00:43:09.369
This also causes the valves
that separate the upper part

00:43:09.369 --> 00:43:12.836
and the lower part of the
heart to not form properly.

00:43:12.836 --> 00:43:16.590
Instead of two valves,
there's only one large valve.

00:43:16.590 --> 00:43:20.622
The hearts of people with
an AV canal must work harder

00:43:20.622 --> 00:43:23.782
than a typical heart which can
cause it to become enlarged

00:43:23.782 --> 00:43:25.615
if it is not repaired.

